Cyberpunk style: A glowing holographic Apple logo floats above a dark workspace, its surface fragmented and reconstructed with exposed circuit pathways and neon blue energy lines. Surrounding it, translucent floating panels display cascading configuration code in electric cyan and magenta. In the foreground, an old-school coffee mug sits on a sleek black desk, steam rising and morphing into binary patterns. The background reveals a rain-streaked window overlooking a dense cityscape of towering servers with pulsing data streams connecting them like neural pathways. A robotic arm reaches from the shadows, delicately holding a glowing microchip that bridges two incompatible connector types—one angular and modern, one rounded and legacy. The entire scene is bathed in contrasting warm amber from a desk lamp and cool electric blues from the holographic displays, creating dramatic shadows and highlighting the tension between old and new technology architectures.
